                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d608">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.796/321: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Vincent</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-05-13T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 13, 1943—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>613. Reference Embassy’s telegram no. 607, April 27, 11 a.m., in regard to
                    British proposal to operate a number of RAF transport planes out of Chungking,
                    Kweilin and Lanchow.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>The Department believes above proposal is the same one made by the British
                        in Washington in February of this year, which, according to the British, was
                        based on a request made by the Chinese Embassy at London to supply a number
                        of transport planes for service in China.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>It has now been ascertained that the British Air Ministry and the London
                        Munitions Assignments Board dropped this proposal early in March and that no
                        further action on the Chinese request is contemplated by the British.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
